- **Access, portability, and correction**: While signed in, you may review and edit personal information and record content that the product lets you edit (subject to feature design). You may also contact us via Section 10 of this Policy and, where permitted by applicable law, request a copy of your personal data.

- **Right to deletion**: You may use “Delete account” on member/account screens to request termination of the Service and deletion of information linkable to you; the app will prompt you to confirm. For scope and timing—including when geographic or coordinate‑related data may still remain—see Section 9 (“Data retention & deletion”). **Even if you delete a bookkeeping row or request erasure, that does not by itself restore recognition quota already consumed under the Terms of Service (EULA):** purchases, deduction ledgers and anti‑abuse logs may be **briefly retained in minimised form** under Section 9 and applicable law. That is separate from whether a ledger line disappears in the UI.

- **Right to restrict processing and refuse use**: You may contact us at any time to request that we stop collecting, processing, or using your personal data, or to withdraw consent for particular features. Withdrawing consent or restricting use of necessary data may make some features unavailable. Where commercial communications are allowed by law, we will provide a way to opt out.

- **Cross-border transfers**: To operate the Service, you understand that your personal data and bookkeeping content are hosted primarily with our entrusted cloud infrastructure (Supabase); the primary region is **Japan (Tokyo)**. Such transfers are reasonably necessary to provide the service you requested, support cloud synchronization, and perform backups. We apply required access controls and safeguards under applicable law and this Policy.


