## 9. Data retention and deletion

- When you actively apply to delete your account within the application, we will remove the original copy of the personal data and content linked to your account from the operating server environment within a reasonable period, in principle no more than thirty (30) calendar days, and such deletion cannot be restored through the general user interface.

- To the extent necessary for compliance with regulations, accounting, auditing, information security or dispute resolution, some records may be temporarily retained for the duration of the purpose or kept after anonymization/de-identification; after the purpose is eliminated, they will be deleted or further irreversibly de-identified.

- **Recognition quotas, in‑app purchases, and antifraud minimised records**: To **perform contracts** (including the Terms of Service (EULA) on recognition consumption, purchase consideration and anti‑abuse), **prevent fraud**, support **audit, tax or dispute evidence**, and cooperate with regulators where compulsory law requires, these items may persist only as **field‑limited short‑term records**—or irreversibly aggregated statistics—until the underlying purpose lapses: **in‑app purchase or point top‑up transaction references / order IDs, recognition deduction/balance journals (including timestamps and server-side corroboration), anomaly and abuse‑prevention logs, and security‑audit access traces.** Retaining them **does not** imply that deleting a bookkeeping row from the UI or invoking erasure **automatically** restores quota already consumed in line with the Terms, resets add‑on purchase hurdles, or changes storefront refunds; entitlement follows contract and platform rules—not only whether an entry remains visible.

- Account deletion mainly removes data "that can identify you personally or be linked to your account"; however, location and latitude and longitude information that has been de-identified and aggregated by geocoding, location matching or statistical purposes, or has been detached from a specific account, and is public or shared by multiple people, may still exist in databases, geocoding service caches, indexes, or general geographic data generated by third-party map/geographic service processing. Such data is not the subject of your exclusive data rights, nor is it property "exclusively yours"; it may continue to be retained as long as it complies with laws and service necessity. If there are other provisions in laws or this platform's policies or if you make a substantiated request in accordance with the law, we will still handle it to the extent feasible.


